summary: Of all the things the queen of Winterfell thought she would have to deal with that day, chasing a pig, who was chasing Arya, was...
question: Of all the things the queen of Winterfell thought she would have to deal with that day, chasing a pig, who was chasing Arya, was certainly not high on her list.
answer:
Of all the things the queen of Winterfell thought she would have to deal with that day, chasing a pig, who was chasing Arya, was certainly not high on her list.


“My bet is on Lady Arya!”


Sansa spared a glance back to glare at Tormund Giantsbane, who had the cheek to roar with laughter. Next to him, Jon raised his tankard as if to say, What can you do with a Wildling?


“You cannot teach them table manners, that’s for sure,” Sansa huffed just as Arya shimmied up the nearest post, standing with her hands on her hips.


She cupped her hands to her mouth and shouted, “Reeee!”


The pig turned in its tracks and charged at Sansa, who covered her eyes. There was a loud, wet sound, and the pig’s head went rolling down the stones, coming to a rest at her feet.


Sansa opened her eyes to stare dumbly at Ser Podrick Payne, who wiped off his sword and bowed, a blush staining his fair cheek. She intimated Arya with a slight incline of her head, still standing on the post amidst racuous cheers.


Podrick stepped back, seemingly blindsided by Sansa’s favor. His broad back hit the post, Arya lost her balance, and toppled into the midden.


Ignoring the vengeful look her sister bestowed upon her, Sansa proclaimed, “It seems we shall be roasting a pig for the feast tonight.”


If anyone wondered why the youngest Lady Stark was eating an apple in the morning as she shot sly looks at her sister, it was anyone’s guess.

answer:

Arya already is as beautiful as Sansa.

GRRM hits that point across with a hammer throughout all five books.

body:
Another thing missing from 8x04 was Arya dealing with the fact that Beric Dondarrion, a man she hated for years and who was on her list died protecting her. Beric gave his life so she could fulfill her destiny. Beric sacrificed himself so Arya could save humanity and tell death to go fuck itself.

AND THEY DIDN’T EVEN ACKNOWLEDGE HIM AFTER 8x03.

title: Villains defeated by the Starks
body:
Joffrey Baratheon - Killed by Olenna Tyrell after Sansa told her what a monster he was

Meryn Trant - Killed by Arya Stark

Walder Frey - Killed by Arya Stark

Locke - Killed by Bran Stark while warging into Hodor

Karl Tanner - Killed by Jon Snow

Rast - Killed by Ghost

Janos Slynt - Killed by Jon Snow

Roose Bolton - Killed by Ramsay, in large part due to Sansa reminding him that Roose’s trueborn son would always have a stronger claim, and also her escape

Ramsay Bolton - Killed by Sansa Stark

Littlefinger - Killed by Sansa Stark, with the help of Bran and Arya

Euron Greyjoy - Killed by Jaime Lannister, who returned to KL after Sansa told him that Cersei was going to be executed

The Waif - Killed by Arya Stark

Alliser Thorne - Killed by Jon Snow

Night King - Killed by Arya Stark, with help from Bran’s 3ER abilities, Jon’s rally of troops, and Sansa’s push to take back Winterfell

The Mountain - Killed by the Hound, who was able to do so because Arya refused to mercy-kill him

Daenerys Targaryen - Killed by Jon Snow after everyone and their mother pointed out that she would be aiming at Sansa next

The Starks saved the world and rid it of several monsters. They really did that shit. Ned would be so proud.
